problem:
Compute all values of $b$ for which the following system has a solution $(x,y)$ in real numbers:
\begin{align*}
\sqrt{xy} &= b^b, \\
\log_b (x^{\log_b y}) + \log_b (y^{\log_b x}) &= 4b^4.
\end{align*}

Let \[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
n^2-2 & \text{ if }n<0, \\
2n-20 & \text{ if }n \geq 0.
\end{array}
\right.\]What is the positive difference between the two values of $a$ that satisfy the equation $f(-2)+f(2)+f(a)=0$?

Point $P$ is selected at random from the interior of the pentagon with vertices $A=(0,2)$, $B= (4,0)$, $C = (2\pi +1, 0)$, $D=(2\pi
+1,4)$, and $E=(0,4)$. What is the probability that $\angle APB$ is obtuse? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
pair A,B,C,D,I;
A=(0,2);
B=(4,0);
C=(7.3,0);
D=(7.3,4);
I=(0,4);
draw(A--B--C--D--I--cycle);
label("$A$",A,W);
label("$B$",B,S);
label("$C$",C,E);
label("$D$",D,E);
label("$E$",I,W);
[/asy]

Two circles of radius $r$ are externally tangent to each other and internally tangent to the ellipse $x^2 + 5y^2 = 6,$ as shown below. Find $r.$
[asy]
size(7cm);
draw(scale(sqrt(6), sqrt(6)/sqrt(5))* unitcircle);
draw((0,-1.5)--(0,1.7),EndArrow);
draw((-3,0)--(3,0),EndArrow);
draw(Circle( (sqrt(0.96),0), sqrt(0.96) ));
draw(Circle( (-sqrt(0.96),0), sqrt(0.96) ));
label("$x$",(3,0),E);label("$y$",(0,1.7),N);
[/asy]

Let \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
-x + 3 & \text{if } x \le 0, \\
2x - 5 & \text{if } x > 0.
\end{array}
\right.\]How many solutions does the equation $f(f(x)) = 4$ have?

In the diagram, $\triangle PQR$ is right-angled at $P$ and has $PQ=2$ and $PR=2\sqrt{3}$.  Altitude $PL$ intersects median $RM$ at $F$.  What is the length of $PF$? [asy]
