Chuck the llama is tied to the corner of a $2\text{ m}$ by $3\text{ m}$ shed on a $3\text{ m}$ leash. How much area (in square meters) does Chuck have in which to play if he can go only around the outside of the shed? [asy]
draw((0,0)--(15,0)--(15,10)--(0,10)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
draw((15,10)--(27,19),black+linewidth(1));
dot((27,19));
label("Shed",(7.5,5));
label("CHUCK",(27,19),N);
label("2",(0,0)--(0,10),W);
label("3",(0,0)--(15,0),S);
label("3",(15,10)--(27,19),SE);
[/asy]

What is the number of centimeters in the length of $EF$ if $AB\parallel CD\parallel EF$?

[asy]

size(4cm,4cm);
pair A,B,C,D,E,F,X;

A=(0,1);
B=(1,1);
C=(1,0);
X=(0,0);
D=(1/3)*C+(2/3)*X;

draw (A--B--C--D);
draw(D--B);
draw(A--C);

E=(0.6,0.4);
F=(1,0.4);

draw(E--F);

label("$A$",A,NW);
label("$B$",B,NE);
label("$C$",C,SE);
label("$D$",D,SW);
label("$E$",shift(-0.1,0)*E);
label("$F$",F,E);

label("$100$ cm",midpoint(C--D),S);
label("$150$ cm",midpoint(A--B),N);

[/asy]

The orthocenter of triangle $ABC$ divides altitude $\overline{CF}$ into segments with lengths $HF = 6$ and $HC = 15.$  Calculate $\tan A \tan B.$

[asy]
unitsize (1 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, H;

A = (0,0);
B = (5,0);
C = (4,4);
D = (A + reflect(B,C)*(A))/2;
E = (B + reflect(C,A)*(B))/2;
F = (C + reflect(A,B)*(C))/2;
H = extension(A,D,B,E);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(C--F);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$F$", F, S);
dot("$H$", H, W);
[/asy]

The figure shows rectangle $ABCD$ with segment $PQ$ dividing the rectangle into two congruent squares. How many right triangles can be drawn using three of the points $\{A,P,B,C,Q,D\}$ as vertices? [asy]
draw((0,0)--(8,0)--(8,4)--(0,4)--cycle);
draw((4,0)--(4,4));
label("D",(0,0),S);
label("Q",(4,0),S);
